  "text": "Several recent studies have suggested that false-positives in HTS campaigns can account for a substantial proportion of HTS hits. [CITATION_1] Further annotation of the hits identified by this screen is therefore required to ensure that they are inhibiting FEN1 specifically. False-positive results may arise through several different mechanisms, including aggregation, destabilization of protein structure, or redox activity. Furthermore, many of the hits identified in the FEN1 HTS may act through intercalation of substrate DNA, rather than specific inhibition of FEN1.",
